TY  - JOUR
TI  - Continuity of Equilibria for Production Economies: New Results
AU  - Fuchs, Gérard
AB  - [It has already been proven that when production is described by differentiable supply functions, the equilibrium correspondence is continuous for "most" economies [7 and 8]. The present paper generalizes this result to situations where production activities are described through a certain class of correspondences: namely, those which have a smooth graph and are such that the profit function is differentiable.]
